The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 12 May is 42,091 (4,871.8 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 07 May, there were 112 new confirmed cases (13.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 30 April, there were 131 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 15% (19 fewer cases).
